This is how Italian food is supposed to look, feel, and taste. A friend and I arrived at Noodle Pudding looking for an authentic serving of Italian cuisine that moved beyond the typical New York City pizza slice. There was a queue out the door, however service was moving fast, and we were seated within fifth teen minutes! Noodle Pudding, despite its misleading name, is classic old school Italian in terms of ambience, service, and quality. The menu is relatively small, but packed full of diverse flavours from across the region, with curated choices including a beautiful Rabbit Ragu dish which you wouldn’t generally find at more mainstream Italian venues. All of the food we ordered was presented simply, but effectively, and absolutely sang with flavour - it’s clear that Noodle Pudding take great care with regard to the quality of their dishes - the food here is just like how nonna would make it. A restaurant not to be missed when visiting New York!

The common saying "Don't judge a book by its cover" would seem to apply perfectly to Noodle Pudding. However, rather confusingly, Noodle Pudding doesn't even seem to have a cover to judge it by - there's no signage on the front of the store, no clues that inside these doors is a fresh, flavorful restaurant; almost as if you had gone home to your grandmothers and she had put out a place setting for anyone walking in off the street. While most restaurants try to burnish their family focused chops, Noodle Pudding puts it front and center, sourcing in ingredients from local farms in New Jersey and "proudly" not accepting credit cards.  We had the fried zucchini flowers as an appetizer, filled with ricotta cheese and lightly fried mixing salty and sweet together. For a main course, I chose the Fettuccine with mussels, clams and shrimp in a shellfish ragu sauce. Amazingly spicy with a full plate of seafood, each piece almost falling out of the shell, and coated in the ragu sauce, I didn't stop eating until the plate was clean. Finally over cappuccinos and espressos, we shared a delicious sweet peaches and vanilla ice cream.

I haven't had a meal out this satisfying in a long time. My friend suggested this place for dinner as she had a good experience the last time she dined here, and I must agree. The entire meal was absolutely delicious.  That being said, here are some notes about this place: - They are only open for dinner - from 5:30pm - They only take cash - They don't take reservations for parties of 6 or less - They invite you to go and wait for a table  After a 45 minute wait for a table, my three friends and I finally got settled into a nice, rear-alcove, corner table. Our waiter came by to recommend one pasta special, but said the rest was whatever was on the menu. We went completely with the menu items, decided to share everything, and ordered the following:  - Razor Clams Oreganata (4) - Clean, delicate clam flavor, dressed with a crust of seasoned bread crumbs and a squeeze of lemon juice. Yummy starter!  - Crispy-Fried NJ Whiting (2) - Two crispy-fried whole whiting. I took half of one whiting with the head and ate the entire head! That's how delicate this fish was! Delicious!  - Fried Calamari with Spicy Aioli and Lemon Wedge - Crispy, nicely-battered, good texture/bite to the calamari without being too chewy. Nicely flavored Aioli to go along with it, but not spicy at all to my palate.  - Hand-cut Linguini with Clams, Zucchini, Cherry Tomatoes and Fresh Pepper - Homemade, al dente pasta with fresh clams so clean that they were delicate in flavor. The zucchini and cherry tomatoes added another layer of freshness and texture. The entire dish together tasted more like a light pasta primavera because there was very little clam flavor coming from the clams. It could have used a dash of clam juice, but it was still good.  - Pappardelle Alla Vaccinara (oxtail ragu) with Pecorino Shavings - Homemade, al dente pasta coated with oxtail meat stewed tender. A hearty, meaty, chewy, flavorful bite with each forkful. This has a heavier, comforting mouthfeel compared to the pasta dish above. I liked having both of these dishes as a contrast in flavors and textures.  - Roasted Whole Porgy - What my friends and I especially liked about Noodle Pudding was all of their locally sourced seafood. Not only do you support local fisheries and eat sustainable species, you eat the freshest caught seafood! This whole roasted Porgy was perfectly cooked! Evenly cooked and slightly crispy skin enveloped flaky, white, tender meat. Simply seasoned with a few rosemary sprigs inside its belly, the meat was still moist but fell off the bones easily. I love fish head, so I picked all of best morsels off of the entire fish head, especially the eyes! Fish lovers will love this dish!  Dessert was: - Ricotta Cheesecake - More of a floured cake than a cheesecake, this delicious slice had bits of candied fruit that you would typically find in Panettone. Lightly sweet and moist, it also had bits of lemony flavor, which likely comes from the Citron. A lovely dessert that I would order again.  - Panna Cotta with Fresh Berries - Silky, lightly sweet, and light are the best three ways to describe Noodle Pudding's take on my favorite dessert. Everytime I see panna cotta on the menu, I always havta order it. This one did not disappoint! The fresh berries that went along with it were sweet and ripe. A great complement!  Overall, I had a delicious time at Noodle Pudding. Needless to say, I will be returning for more.

We ordered 14 different dishes, a bottle of wine, and I had a dessert port and every single thing was incredible. We didn't have to wait for a table, but when I go back I'd be happy to.
Awesome relaxed ambience, everything was delicious!! Cheerful, lively, excellent service, knowledgeable staff.
Great Italian food. Definitely recommended
Good Italian food, warm service, many regulars here. Only downside is that it is cash only. People said it gets very busy but it's fine to visit a weekday around 6pm. They don't open for lunch
Delicious
Waiters are unfriendly, serve someone else's order, menu never changes
Best noodles I've ever had, great atmosphere, good service, and the best food.
Great restaurant. Very crowded but it pays to wait.

The service by Ann was stellar, and the timing of food was great, but the gnocchi al pomodoro (overcooked and lacking flavor) and shrimp risotto (undercooked) didn't meet expectations. The tiramisu was good and the ricotta pumpkin cheesecake was more like pumpkin pie than cheesecake.
Ruddest maitre d ever!  Incredibly stuck up, should get out of service business!!!

While I’ll make it a life goal to return here for the food alone, it will be in equal measure to meet the staff again. With genuine attention and a generous side of deadpan humor - food apparently is apparently a whole lot more fun. You need to go here, too.
Wonderful experience
Overpriced, rejecting to give an invoice, possibly evading taxes.
I had to leave a dinner early to catch a flight, and I was devastated, because everything I had so far was delicious, and I can only imagine what I missed out on. I will be going back!
Fantastic Neapolitan Cuisine with great menu choices!  loved it.

-Friendly staff -Great bread/ dipping sauce (but we had to ask for it) -Got the Gnocchi with butter and sage (after reading all the rave reviews)-- it was good, but both my friend and I received the dishes and they were barely warm, if not cold. - My other friend got the risotto, which was a big hit. -Overall, it was a good dining experience, but I think that without the glass of wine before (while waiting for a table) and the bottle of wine during dinner, I would have been a little bit more sensitive to the pitfalls.
No sign on the door. But walk in and find fresh salt.of earth Italian food - not just a red sauce place.
Great! Just great! Always have a dinner if not two dinners when I visit my sister!
Fantastic Neapolitan Cuisine with great menu choices!

I think it's one of the worst restaurants in the Heights. I was served burnt blackened lasagna & could not get a waiter's attention to return it. Also, their cash only policy is not consumer friendly. Returned several times wipeople who insisted on going there. Always a bad food experience & the noise level is unbelievable.

I used to really like this pleasant family friendly restaurant. Unfortunately the food quality and selection has taken a nose dive. Because I loved this place so much I have returned even after disappointing meals. I can now officially say I'm done.
Had the lobster risotto that was really good. Didn't care for the limoncello.
This place is the best.  Fantastic fresh, delicious Italian food.
Great pasta.
Italian comfort food at it's best.
Staff and owner are wonderful. Family style dining great for a small or large group
Great original Italian cuisine
Old school Italian restaurant serving very good food
Really nice high end place. Professional wait staff and pleasant atmosphere .
Great old school Italian restaurant, but can stand up to modern Brooklyn tastes.
Delicious Italian food. Best Martini I've ever had. In. My. Life!
Food was great the waiter very nice

Noodle Pudding is a neighborhood Italian restaurant that keeps getting better every year. It offers amazing seafood, scrumptious pasta, exciting specials, and wonderful service. My only complaint is that the wine by the glass could use some improving. Come early or the wait could take a long time. They don't take reservations for small parties.
The food.is very fresh so good mmm

Took a walk with a friend of mine to Brooklyn and we were famished and looking for a nice place to eat. We could not find better. Fantastic service, fantastic food and typical Italian restaurant. They do not take credit card but this is the beauty of this great authentic Italian restaurant. I recommend the veal parpadelle
Tasty authentic Italian food with great specials and mains.
Treat yourself to a steak.

Dinner with my wife and daughter who is living in Brooklyn for a 4 month college co-op. Best restaurant experience I have had in a long time. Server was engaging and gladly helped us make some meal substitutions. Food was excellent. Atmosphere was warm and charming. A little noisy but we were fine. We were never rushed and thoroughly enjoyed ourselves.

Just love everything about it , all the staff are so professional with a great attitude and nothing seems to ruffle their feathers, everything on the menu is excellent though I have my favorites as obviously everyone does as you'll see many customers without menus, never had anything other than an excellent meal and my friends only brought me there for the first time a year ago , what a shame !!

The ambiance is classic Italian but they don't dish the food. That's a tad disappointing since classic Italian restaurants are all about service. Food is great but service is mediocre.  They didn't even offer pepper or parm, just left it on the table. Still tipped 20%...jerks.

Noodle Pooding has respect for food ! I am a Real Estate Broker and run around all over New York, I have eaten in so many restaurants from Staten Island to Harlem and this is the only place where I can relax and enjoy my meal every time! There is a certain feeling of trust; always clean always fresh, always delicious!
(Translated by Google) Familiar, excellent quality of the abundant dishes. Very good service.  (Original) Familiar, excelente calidad de los abundantes platos. Muy buen servicio.
(Translated by Google) Italian food with real Italian flavor. If they are nearby, do not forget to visit.  (Original) Comida Italiana con sabor real italiano. Si están cerca no dejes de visitar.

What can be said about Noodle Pudding that hasn't already been said?  Excellent Italian food and reasonable prices in a nice space with good service. Kind of a dumb name - people always think it's a Kugel place when I say the name. There often is a wait - go at off-times if you can or prepare to wait.  Oh, and it's CASH ONLY.
The place is off the charts!  The food is the best!   Tony sei bravo!!!!!
Awesome fresh home made Italian food. Cash only. Definitely worth the wait!

Cash only!  Great Italian restaurant in the neighborhood. Stumbled to this cute place after spending a day at the near by park.  For a Sunday night a table for 2, we were quickly seated without reservation, which was actually a surprise because it was bumping when we arrived.  The service here was quick and attentive, was offered a basket of bread and water once seated. I ordered a bruschetta for the table, and special pasta dish -  orecchiette with meatball and basil, and a simple angel hair pasta with garlic and evoo and a pork chop dish. All were phenomenal, the pork was slightly drier than I prefer but it was nicely sear and delicious with a side of veggies and mash.

(Translated by Google) Amazing place and excellent food !! Impossible not to eat one night if you are close.  (Original) Increíble el lugar y la comida excelente!! Imposible no ir a comer una noche si estás cerca.

One of the best eating place in Brooklyn heights!No reservation and Cash only! No credit cards accepted. The filet of Salmon is the best and also pasta dishes. May be 45 minutes waiting time but worth it!

Fabulous experience -- we had a party of 13, they gave us a pre-selection of appetizers that were terrific and then we ordered individual main courses.  Homemade pastas, authentic Italian food and great gluten free options. Great experience.
Cash-only here, so don't forget to go to the ATM before coming here. Love the lasagna, and tomato & mozzarella.
The food here is fresh and tasty, the prices are great, and the staff are lovely.
Delicious food. Wonderful atmosphere, but most of all, the staff and the patrons are all lovely people. What a gem.

I hesitated to leave this review, as I don't want more people finding out about it! The food here is fresh and tasty, the prices are great, and the staff are lovely. It's always busy so you will have to wait. But it's worth it.

poor and very slow service! food itself is decent, but not amazing to make our wait worth it...our group of 4 waited 2 hours from stepping foot in the restaurant to getting our food! it's also cash only...
You will not find a better meal or experience in all of NYC.  This place is legit.  Come early because there is always a wait.  Mostly locals eating here..it really is that good.
Great food. Cash only.

Great food. Great service. Great atmosphere. And astoundingly cheap, for the most part. Must-try in Brooklyn. Most of the pasta is made fresh in-house and is delicious, but you can't go wrong. If you're big in fish, try the catch of the day specials.

This is my favorite restaurant. Lots of locals from Brooklyn Heights. Great and very reasonably priced Italian food. Open front windows in summer. Takes reservations for big groups. Usually has a holiday theme of some kind. Staff turnover is practically zero; this place doesn't change much.

Friendly service, with good food. They only accept cash, so plan accordingly. Plates of food  run about $15-20 on average. My wife ordered a salad and was a little disappointed with it, only because for the price it was just lettuce (though thats what salad is ;-). Otherwise, the food was delicious. Service was friendly and quick to seat us and take care of our needs. We had a party of 8, and we were seated, ate, and paid in less than an hour. It is a place that we felt we could have lingered, but had to go due to prior arrangements. I would return again.
Amazing food and ambiance! Pls note its CASH ONLY!
Had a B Cleanliness Rating, and the sign was not posted by the door to see, like it should be.
Neighborhood institution. Great food. No reservations. Cash only. Service acts like you'll come back no matter what you do, because the food is so good you likely will.
Solid Italian restaurant in the Heights

The hostdess was on the phone and left a few of use waiting. Saved by a brilliant waiter - no harm done. Was a little patronising by explaining to us what bolognese is (we have travelled to Italy  often) but was not intentional. Loved the food and atmosphere - will go again next time i'm in Brooklyn.
Solid quality Italian food, good flavors and textures, but didn't quite live up to the hype. Atmosphere was fun, casual and family friendly.
No cards.. Cash only and YES, they do reservations more than 6 ppl only.. ♡♡
Nothing special. Overhyped place, extremely loud, will not come back.
excellent Italian food. expect to have to wait a bit to get a table, and remember that it's cash only.
I love this place. Food is amazing and the atmosphere is outstanding. I love everything about this place
Good Italian food.

Great Italian food. Feels like you're eating in your Italian grandmothers' dining room -- the decor is kitschy, the service is a weird mix of family-style friendly and brusque, and the food is great. Cash only.

I live in an Italian suburb and Noodle Pudding truly has some of the best food I've ever had. The workers were friendly and enthusiastic. My friends who live in Brooklyn Heights are completely in love with the restaurant. The food is superb and authentic. I recommend this 100% to anyone looking for good Italian food. The wait and price is completely worth it when you get this quality of food.

Reliably good Italian, while one of a few really good ones in the area, it won't too the best Italian joints in all of Brioklyn. For that you must trek south to Bay Ridge/Dyker Heights. I had some of their pasta plates and calamari. I was blown away more by the desserts above all else though.
I loved Antonio the chef. He made my visit like family and made my family a wonderful meal. The swordfish was succulent and the Cappelli with eggplant and fresh tomatoes was just magnificent.
Very old school. Would appreciate some credit card stuff
best thing in Brooklyn

Terrible! My husband and I ordered a dozen clams on the half shell and two entrees. The waitress returned and informed us that they were out of clams, and handed us the menus to make a new selection. While we were eating our dessert, a couple walked in and sat next to us (at 10:00 pm) and was served a platter of a dozen clams on the half shell. When I finally got the attention of my waitress and voiced my concerns, she told me that they probably had those clams in the basement. She sent out a man from the kitchen who told me not to "take it personally," that he knows them and they called ahead and he saved it aside for them. I asked him if a customer wants to ensure that they get something from your menu, they are supposed to know to call ahead and have it put aside??? He argued back "Yes, that's the way it is. Sorry." Clearly the customer is not right, nor are they respected at Noodle Pudding.

No credit cards - but we've paid with local personal checks - no reservations...but still, our neighborhood fave. There's just something about this place that we love. Pro-tip. Vinnie's line caught fish. "That fish was swimming at 11 A.M."
The best traditional Italian food I have ever tried. Everything is fresh and homemade. Black sea bass with clams mussels and shrimp was unbelievable.

Not worth it. The wait was so long as there was no reservation available. No place to sit while you wait. I stood and kept getting hit by the customers and waiters coming through. The head waiter kept telling us that our table was almost ready when it actually wasn't.  Finally we are seated. To even get a waiter's attention was SO difficult that I contemplated leaving. But since I had already waited an hour for this place, what is another 10+ minutes? We ordered. Water does not come until our food comes. AND my ravenous self was staring at the tables near us, THEY ALL GOT BREAD. WHERE WAS OUR BREAD?!?!?  Anyways, so my friend and I got the tagliatelle bolognese as well as the pork belly.  Pork belly was just all fat. NO meat. What kind of dish is this?! I understand that pork belly has a lot of fat.. I've eaten it at a lot of places. But if I order the entree version, I expect some meat on it!  The tagliatelle was less disappointing. It was a homecooked pasta, something you can make yourself. Not exciting. Not innovative. But this place isn't that. I recommend it if you want a down to earth meal.  But you can get this pasta anywhere else in the city, don't suffer through this long wait and horrible service for it.
Awesome

Incredibly charming atmosphere and the food is absolutely unparalleled. It rivals some of the most spectacular authentic restaurants in Italy- I felt as if I had been transported to the cobbled streets of Rome, embarking upon a culinary journey to my old favorite restaurants near the Trevi Fountain. The gnocchi was one of the best pasta dishes I have ever had in my life. Absolutely recommend this, a can't-miss place in Brooklyn!
Great place.    Great service. Great food!
LOVED Noodlye Pudding! Aldo was great and Tony has a great spot! The kids were a bit much, but, it was a nice day in NY. Will always go back!
Love this place. You know a place is excellent when there's no name above the door, you can't make a reservation and can only pay in cash.....yet its still slammed every night.

My favorite restaurant in the entire city. Great ambience; warm and friendly. Gets crowded so go closer to closing when it opens up. Food is always fresh and delicious, with local specials that are simple and wonderful. Like Jersey Tomatoes and onions. Not fancy, just delicious. Cash only but not a place to break the bank--totally reasonable. Don't look for a sign (there isn't one); just look through the beautiful front window and feel drawn in!

Incredible!  Highly recommend the "Trust Tony" menu. Chef Tony prepares his favorites based on whatever great ingredients are available that day.  Our meal included salmon, wild bass, flank steak, octopus salad, stuffed squash blossoms,fresh pasta and more - including home made ricotta, honeydew melon, fresh figs, and honey. Plus 4 wonderful desserts!  Don't think we could have made any version of that meal for the same price.  And his was MUCH BETTER!

Food poisoning.  I had the lasagna last night.  Tasted good, but I was throwing up an hour or so later.  Food poisoning?  I think so and this place has a B grade from the city.  Service was good, but I was charged $12 for a small glass of Chianti but at the bar beforehand was only charged $8.  I didn't want to make a fuss about it because I was on a date, but that combined with the food poisoning made this place a very bad experience

Cramped. Lots of specials on the menu no longer available. Waiter was awkward with us all night, and disappeared for long stretches.  But the worst was when we sent back a bottle of wine which was legitimately not right, and the manager actually challenged us on it & said the wine was fine. $25 bottle of wine, I might add.  Even with decent food, in Brooklyn Heights with so many other good places, who would put up with that?
the bread alone is worth a write up.  great food but get there early.  only draw back is that this is a cash only place.  i like alot and have been 4 times already for the year.

Not sure why its called noodle pudding since I dont think there is any pudding on the menu but the noodles are real good.  Ask your waitress/waiter which ones are fresh for the night and order ones of those.  Service is good, attentative and friendly.  The ambiance is great.  Price is fair except they don't take credit cards. Portion size is good--not huge but enough that you will definately be full.  As for the pastas, they do 1/2 orders which is great so if you can't decide between which to order, get the half sizes.  We ordered the seafood rissoto and the fettucine with shell fish.  Both were very good and heavy on the seafood.
very good food but service was slow.  they had a nice cheap house wine!
